The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Party time for stocks 
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Party time for stocks 
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                                            
	Mumbai, Aug. 19: The sensex leapt almost 200 points to scale a two-and-a-half-year peak  the euphoria coinciding with Parsi New Year even as the markets optimism was underpinned by strong global cues, the easing of food inflation and strong monsoon-induced economic growth forecasts.        
	Cement, financial services and fast-moving consumer goods stocks fuelled todays rally that saw the bellwether open strong at 18276.50. It rappelled up quickly to a high of 18475.27 before ending at 18454.94  a gain of 197.82 points and its best closing since February 5, 2008.         
	Over the past two sessions, the index has rallied over 400 points.         
	On the NSE, the Nifty breached the 5500 mark to finish at 5540.20, a rise of 1.11 per cent. An added reason was the participation of heavyweights such as Reliance Industries.        
	The indices rose for the second day in a row as investor sentiment improved after food inflation eased to 10.35 per cent for the week ended August 7, amid speculation that the monsoon will boost crop output, buoying economic growth. Easing inflation may reduce the pressure on the central bank for further monetary action to rein in inflation, brokerage Sharekhan said.        
	Banking stocks were the highlight of the days trading session with HDFC Bank hitting a lifetime high. Shares of the bank touched a high of Rs 2,240 before ending at Rs 2,231.15, a gain of Rs 42.70. The rally was also seen in other counters such as ICICI Bank, which hit a yearly high of Rs 1,015 and subsequently closed at Rs 1,012.55, a rise of Rs 42.50 over its last close.                                                                                                                                       
